Foraging mulberries in another secret spot of organic fruit farms...learning about agroforestry biodiversity 😋🌱

Doing stuff...5am hike under a  pitch black, star spangled sky...a golden sunrise, where the mountains meet the sea...barefoot in the green meadows of tree labyrinths...eating from organic fruit gardens, learning  from plant geniuses...in awe of the biodiversity and everything being as it should, in harmony...

All the magic that is you...you are sunshine 🌞, moonbeams 🌙, rainbows 🌈 and pure love ❤️ making life more colorful and fun, since the day you entered this world 19 years ago...love you my Dylan Bleu 🎂🎈🎉💕

Happy day after...the gift that keeps on giving, is giving...and love, which costs nothing. Our annual holiday visit to @animalhaven 🐶🐱is always a bit heartbreaking but the best part of my holiday because giving love is my favorite, and it gives me hope- these animals are resilient and so forgiving, and there are people who selflessly dedicate their time to ensure their well being. A big shout out to all of the staff and volunteers who work tirelessly to keep these animals healthy and safe; and to the foster families who open their hearts and homes; to everyone who has helped keep the shelter running...adoptees and those who donate money. This is what the holidays (and everyday) are all about 🙏🏻🕊

There are living angels that walk the earth and I can honestly say that Leonard Lauder is one of them. From the moment we met, 20 years ago, he has been my friend, mentor, protector and champion; encouraging me to be the best version of myself, from the inside out. He is honest, sincere, whippet smart, inspiring, generous and no bulls#*t a rarity of a gentleman. Thank you Leonard for uplifting and celebrating women, we celebrate you; and may any man take pages out of your book (which I really hope you write one soon). It was an honor to take stage and speak of you (although I felt like I would hurl from nerves) but anything for you, I love you to the moon and back ♥️
